        "author": {
          "name": "Frank Zago",
          "email": "fzago@cray.com",
          "date": "2014-06-20 17:23:26.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-07-20 18:39:00.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5252: Do not unconditionally delete the HSM event fifo",
        "message": "LU-5252: Do not unconditionally delete the HSM event fifo\n\nThe lustreapi HSM library will use a pipe if it already exists.\nHowever the deregistration will unconditionally delete that pipe,\nwhich is not correct.\n\nAn admin may want to create the pipe with certain rights/ownership,\nwhich the llapi_hsm_register_event_fifo() doesn't allow. In that case,\nllapi_hsm_unregister_event_fifo() should not delete it.\n\nChange-Id: I487f6efea06c6f6bc88b2f838153c0239e369461\nSigned-off-by: frank zago <fzago@cray.com>\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/10809\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
